TopicTitle: From where do you get your data?

Articles.Content:
I'm curious, when you are searching for something in particular about rocketry, where do you search on the net? Post your linkz!

I'm mostly interested in soviet stuff, so these are the ones I open up frequently :

http://www.russianspaceweb.com/

http://www.astronautix.com/

http://space.skyrocket.de/

When I remember any new ones, I'll post them too here.

PS:A bit off-topic... but arent these 2 pages from astronautix kinda... contradicting each other?

http://spaceart1.ning.com/video/n-11-soviet-rocket-speculative-design and http://www.astronautix.com/lvs/n11.htm

Both estimate around the same payload, so it probably is the same design... but why is the 1st stage changed in the 1963 version?
